Binding Energy & Mass Defect · node ATM · ATM · A bound nucleus weighs LESS than its separate parts — the missing mass became binding energy (E=mc²). The curve peaks at iron-56, the most tightly bound nucleus.

universe of origin : ATM · The Atom
seal               : POWERS STARS AND BOMBS. Fusing light nuclei (toward iron) or splitting heavy ones (toward iron) both release that binding energy — fusion lights the Sun, fission runs reactors. It's why ~1% of your mass is pure bound energy, not 'stuff.'
